[{"id":31177,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Teflon","Dacron","Nylon 6, 6","Nylon 6"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Caprolactam is a cyclic amide. Caprolactam when heated at high temperature in presence of water, gives Nylon 6.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0c2f0ecd-80d4-4778-aff2-185aff623301-9895891.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 210px;\" />&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31235,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Both assertion and reason are correct, but the reason is not the correct explanation for the assertion.","Both assertion and reason are correct, and the reason is the correct explanation for the assertion.","Assertion in incorrect statement, but the reason is correct.","Both assertion and reason are incorrect."],"answer":1,"solution":"The strength of cellulose is improved by acetylation and then used for making packing material. Rayon (semisyntehtic polymer of cellulose)&nbsp;has superior properties than natural cotton.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31180,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Protein","Starch","Rubber","Rayon"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Natural polymers<br />These polymers are found in plants and animals. Examples are proteins, cellulose, starch, some resins and rubber.</p><p>Semi synthetic polymers are those polymers that are prepared by chemically treating natural polymers. Rayon is a regenerated cellulosic fibre. So, Rayon is semisynthetic polymer.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31222,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/74cef59b-1ebb-4d60-b10d-0fcd73eba184-image.png\" style=\"width: 260px; height: 121px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de15eadc-e935-46da-ad8e-bfbdd4bd85d5-image.png\" style=\"width: 260px; height: 124px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ca341dba-b878-4bc1-9358-29703282e607-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 83px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ca432efe-754b-4b6d-b69c-441452c39262-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 87px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Nylon 6 is obtained by heating caprolactam&nbsp;with water at a high temperature.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3eb90d6f-7459-43a9-af5c-5f8f3bdf1593-image56.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 150px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31173,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["High density polythene","Polyacrylonitrile","Low density polythene","Polytetrafluoroethane"],"answer":0,"solution":"High-density polyethylene (HDPE) is commonly prepared in the presence of a Ziegler-Natta catalyst.&nbsp;<p>The information provided describes the preparation and characteristics of a high-density polyethylene (HDPE) polymer. HDPE is a widely used thermoplastic polymer known for its high strength, durability, and excellent chemical resistance.</p><p>The presence of trimethylammoniumpropyl (TMP) and titanium tetrachloride (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>TiCl</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>) indicates that the polymerization process is likely carried out using a Ziegler-Natta catalyst system. This catalyst system enables the production of high-density polyethylene by controlling the polymerization conditions.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31215,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Neoprene","Buna <math><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","Nylon <math><mn>6,6</mn></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<table border=\"1px solid\">\t<thead>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<th>Polymers</th>\t\t\t<th>Monomers</th>\t\t</tr>\t</thead>\t<tbody>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>1) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Buna</mi><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></td>\t\t\t<td><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>CN</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td><br />\t\t\t2) Neoprene- <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msub><mo>-</mo></math></td>\t\t\t<td><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5d0edbf8-f26f-460f-8221-99bc08552c60-image.png\" style=\"width: 202px; height: 62px;\" /></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>3) NYLON <math><mo>-</mo><mn>6,6</mn></math>:&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>~</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>CO</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><mi>NH</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>~</mo></math></td>\t\t\t<td><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>&#38;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td><br />\t\t\t4)<br />\t\t\t<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e3ca980e-3e69-4ffb-8971-45e5921df868-image.png\" style=\"width: 419px; height: 116px;\" /><br />\t\t\tIn PHBV, both monomers have chiral centre.</td>\t\t\t<td><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0d28f232-828c-4fd2-a683-22797caf7c2d-image.png\" style=\"width: 295px; height: 151px;\" /><br />\t\t\t<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>oi</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>oi</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></td>\t\t</tr>\t</tbody></table>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31178,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A-II, B-III, C-I, D-IV","A-II, B-I, C-IV, D-III","A-IV, B-III, C-I, D-II","A-IV, B-I, C-III, D-II"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>(A) Rubber is a natural polymer and possesses elastic properties. It is also termed as elastomeric polymer. Neoprene is a family of synthetic rubbers that are produced by the polymerization of chloroprene. So, the correct matching of elastomeric polymer is neoprene.</p><p>(B)&nbsp;Polyesters are the polycondensation products of dicarboxylic acids and diols. Dacron or terylene is the best-known example of polyester.&nbsp;Dacron fibre is crease-resistant and is used in blending with cotton and wool fibres and also as glass reinforcing materials in safety helmets, etc. So, the correct matching of fibre polymer is polyester.</p><p>(C) Thermosetting polymer which cannot be reused or remoulded. Urea formaldehyde resin and phenol-formaldehyde resins are the thermosetting polymers.</p><p>(D)&nbsp;Thermoplastics can soften upon heating and return to their original form on cooling. They&nbsp;are easily moulded and extruded into films, fibres and packaging. Polystyrene is an example of a thermoplastic polymer.</p><p>So the correct matching is A-IV, B-III, C-I, D-II.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31260,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["condensation reaction between monomers","coordinate reaction between monomers","conversion of monomer to monomer ions by protons","hydrolysis of monomers"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":31185,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["isoprene and styrene","neoprene and sulphur","isoprene and sulphur","neoprene and styrene"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Natural rubber may be considered as a linear polymer of isoprene (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-methyl-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>-butadiene) and is also called as cis - <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;- polyisoprene.</p><p>To improve the physical properties, a process of vulcanisation is carried out. This process consists of heating a mixture of raw rubber with sulphur and an appropriate additive at a temperature range between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>373</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>415</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>.&nbsp;</p><p>In the manufacture of tyre rubber, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of sulphur is used as a cross linking agent. The probable structures of vulcanised rubber molecules are depicted below:</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/34130c56-8b3e-4559-aeb3-2fc8e77439c5-9756187_Sol.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 175px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31182,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Ethane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid","Propane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid","Ethane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid","Ethane-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math>-diol and Benzene-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn></math> dicarboxylic acid"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Terylene is a synthetic polyester fibre produced by polymerizing ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid which is obtained from petroleum.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/76c25b12-b858-4403-afc1-ee0ced40062c-9757583_S.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 293px;\" /></p><p>IUPAC name of the ethylene glycol is Ethane-1,2-diol and name of Terephthalic acid is Benzene-1,4-dicarboxylic acid.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31197,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Butadiene-styrene copolymer","Melamine polymer","Neoprene","Poly- <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi></math>-hydroxybutyrate-co- <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi></math>-hydroxyvalerate"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Poly <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi></math>-hydroxybutyrate-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>co</mi></math>- <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi></math>-hydroxy valerate (PHBV) : It is obtained by the copolymerisation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>-hydroxybutanoic acid and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>-hydroxypentanoic acid.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ac3d9001-61a6-4721-9338-94cea2926ab5-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 202px;\" /></p><p>PHBV is used in speciality packaging, orthopaedic devices and in controlled release of drugs. PHBV undergoes bacterial degradation in the environment.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31196,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Dacron","Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>S</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>(a) Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is the polymer of hexamethylene diamine and adipic acid. It is made by the condensation of given monomers.</p><p>(b) Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;os also a condensation polymer of caprolactum. It is a polymide.</p><p>(c) Dacron is also a condensation polymer of ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid. It is an example of polyester.</p><p>(d) Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>S</mi></math>&nbsp;is an addition polymer of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;butadiene and styrene.</p><p>Hence, only (4) is not a condensation polymer.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;(4) is the correct option.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31211,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>(a)&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b76fe7c0-4678-42c8-8646-9369f3b4e0c0-image.png\" style=\"width: 94px; height: 119px;\" />Caprolactum is the monomeric&nbsp;unit of polymer Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p><p>(b) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>Chlorobuta<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></math>diene is the monomeric unit of polymer neoprene.<br />(c) Isoprene is the monomeric unit of polymer natural rubber.<br />(d) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CN</mi></math> (Acrylonitrile) is one of the monomeric unit of polymer&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Buna</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31244,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Amylopectin is a branched polymer of $\\alpha$ - glucose.","Cellulose is a linear polymer of $\\beta$-glucose.","Glycogen is the food reserve of plants.","All proteins are polymers of $\\alpha$ - amino acids."],"answer":2,"solution":"Glycogen is called animal starch and is found in all animal cells. It constitutes the reserve food material.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31225,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uUL_dhYDiY8gQKz4Xxjll8zUIe0d_3lNsYaKCxrB0wY.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/pBqFpIQKpExkkTWHyP0QGz22XLowjaH7W8g21H-D9Qg.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Njb_KRIwBBPsluQRRY5R_73uW2MG1GKUXCTYUDUtuQY.original.fullsize.png\">","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Djv7xMtZOjSYTbL_90laRUyr1PrSUVRjPNS1-R9EcBo.original.fullsize.png\">"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uVYSiv0IKh8WZfQscgtQc5HIUcPZS7c1LozLYb0wiSA.original.fullsize.png\">","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31217,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Polyisobutylene","Polytert-butylene","Polyisobutane","Polyisoprene"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Polyisobutylene is a polymer molecule which is produced by the polymerization of isobutene (also known as 2-methylpropene). The chemical formula of isobutene is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p><p>Polymerization happens according to the following reaction:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/11488f48-c958-4d82-af69-89ae0c30156c-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 168px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31171,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A(II), B(IV), C(I), D(III)","A(II), B(I), C(IV), D(III)","A(IV), B(I), C(III), D(II)","A(IV), B(III), C(I), D(II)"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>chloro<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></math>butadiene can undergo polymerization to form a polymer known as polychloroprene. Polychloroprene&nbsp;is a synthetic rubber commonly known as neoprene.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b3ed2d1f-3c27-4aa6-93b3-22b4b33bc44b.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 81px;\" /></p><p>Polyacrylonitrile (PAN) is an addition polymer. Addition polymers are formed through a polymerization process called addition polymerization, where monomers add to each other without the loss of any small molecules.&nbsp; Nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;Biodegradable polymer.&nbsp;Dacron is a type of polyester. Polyester is a polymer that belongs to the polyester family of polymers.</p><p>So, A-II; B-I; C-IV; D-III</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31229,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Chain growth polymerisation involves homopoly-merisation only","Chain growth polymerisation includes both homo-polymerisation and copolymerisation","Nylon 6 is an example of step-growth polymerisation","Step growth polymerisation requires a bifunctional monomer"],"answer":1,"solution":"The statement (b) is not true. Chain growth polymerisation (or addition polymerisation) involves homopolymerisation only Examples of such polymers include polythene, orlon and teflon.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":31191,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Neoprene","PHBV","Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>","Butadiene-styrene"],"answer":0,"solution":"A copolymer is a polymer formed when two (or more) different types of monomers are linked in the same polymer chain, as opposed to a homopolymer&nbsp;where only one monomer is used.<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/49318ba8-1db4-4f3c-a7dd-f631dacaa4ed-jeeq.png\" style=\"width: 534px; height: 151px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31192,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["It is a linear polymer of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math>-butadiene.","It is obtained by copolymerization of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math> -butadiene and styrene.","It is obtained by copolymerization of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math> -butadiene and acrylonitrile.","The suffix <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> in Buna- <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> stands for its natural occurrence."],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> is formed by the co-polymerization of 1,3-butadiene and vinylcyanide(acrylonitrile)&nbsp;in the presence of a peroxide catalyst.</p><p>It is a synthetic rubber.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1a127715-9005-4514-9572-12e19b5797d5-9708299.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 223px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31184,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Novolacs&nbsp;are phenol-formaldehyde resins with a formaldehyde to phenol molar ratio of less than one.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bce89a9b-2b73-4072-b431-73850e2406b7-image.png\" style=\"width: 487px; height: 280px;\" /></p><p>The rubber obtained is also&nbsp;called Styrene butadiene rubber (SBR). In Buna-S, Bu stands for butadiene and, Na for sodium and S for styrene. It is vulcanised with sulfur. The rubber is slightly inferior to natural rubber in its physical properties.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8e53b179-9e27-4ca1-a4f4-c730da7907a9-image.png\" style=\"width: 379px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>Glyptal- a polyester is formed by ethylene glycol and phthalic acid by step-growth polymerization.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d5455332-73a6-45f9-9fd8-23abe21036aa-image.png\" style=\"width: 527px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>Dacron obtained by condensation polymerisation of ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>420</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>460</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>&nbsp;using zinc acetate and antimony oxide as catalyst.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4e850628-0f8e-44f3-a570-476eab17f3ea-image.png\" style=\"width: 566px; height: 140px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31231,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/934118d5-f71c-4df7-8b3d-0f9ae8c4383a-image.png\" style=\"width: 216px; height: 126px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de7ffaf7-d2e1-4e80-ad73-9324dc6081ab-image.png\" style=\"width: 279px; height: 108px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d07c51ad-6a18-419e-8270-d8eea5f0f057-image.png\" style=\"width: 274px; height: 126px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/11883d6e-1c59-4852-99d6-a190e49c5ae1-image.png\" style=\"width: 274px; height: 129px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"Polymerization takes place through head-head combination.<br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5e47a2b6-db17-4d2b-8609-996bd0addf6d-2018apr15mains.png\" style=\"width: 711px; height: 112px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null}]